section.section:
If a transfer of all personal property or all the stock in business of a business occurs on or after the date of finality and before the semiannual date of finality the property is assessed to the transferee as if the property were escaped property under § 8-417 of this article, if the transferor or the transferee files with the Department or the supervisor on or before the October 1 immediately after the date of the transfer a report, under oath, that contains:
a description of the personal property from the assessment roll;
the date and manner of transfer;
the name and address of the transferee;
the consideration; and
any other information that the Department requires.
